  "stakes": "India's biggest week of the summer — a Super 1000, a defending men's doubles champion, and Sindhu's first real test since the rebuild began.",
  "summary": "**Satwik–Chirag** arrive at Istora having won the Singapore Open three days ago — the form pair on the world tour, world #3, and the only Indian pair to have ever won this event (2023). A back-to-back would be career-defining.\n\n**Lakshya Sen** is seeded inside the top eight in singles, and the draw has handed him Kunlavut Vitidsarn in round one — a rematch of last year's bruising All England encounter. **HS Prannoy** opens against Anders Antonsen, the defending champion. **PV Sindhu** plays her first Super 1000 since the injury layoff, against Wang Zhi Yi — the same opponent who knocked her out at the Asian Games.\n\nNine Indian entries across five disciplines. Istora's crowd is the loudest in badminton, and it almost always falls in love with the underdog. That usually works in India's favour.",
